# Proxy Apple Pay domain verification through Supabase Edge Function.
# Lovable's hosting excludes dot-directories (.well-known/) from the build output,
# so the static file in public/.well-known/ is never served. The Edge Function
# holds the file content and the 200 rewrite keeps the original URL intact
# (Apple/Tap fetches /.well-known/... and must receive a 200, not a redirect).
/.well-known/apple-developer-merchantid-domain-association  https://gifovgwlxwuiibfzyvwb.supabase.co/functions/v1/apple-pay-verify  301

/datafeed.xml https://gifovgwlxwuiibfzyvwb.supabase.co/functions/v1/meta-product-feed 301

# Per-locale HTML shell for /en/*.
# A Vite closeBundle plugin (see vite.config.ts) generates dist/en/index.html
# with <html lang="en" dir="ltr"> alongside the regular dist/index.html
# (which has lang="ar"). Without these rewrite rules, Lovable's default SPA
# fallback serves dist/index.html for every unknown path — meaning /en/*
# would still get the Arabic shell and validators (technicalseo.com, Bing
# first-pass, etc.) report lang="ar" on English URLs.
#
# 200 rewrites (not 301/302) preserve the URL in the address bar — the
# user stays on /en/about while the host internally serves /en/index.html.
# The trailing `!` forces the rewrite even when a file exists at the
# requested path (which isn't actually possible for SPA routes, but
# explicit is better than implicit).
/en          /en/index.html   200
/en/*        /en/index.html   200!
